EKS Upgrade Automation
Change Management Automation Epic — User Stories
Story 1: Convert EKS Upgrade Documentation to Structured Markdown
Checklist
As a platform engineer,
I want the existing EKS upgrade documentation converted into a structured markdown checklist,
So that the validation automation has a machine-readable source of truth for upgrade gates.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
1. Existing upgrade docs (Confluence or Wiki) are exported and converted to markdown
2. Each validation item is represented as a checklist item (- [ ] item)
3. Checklist is organized by category (pre-upgrade checks, node group checks, add-on compatibility,
post-upgrade validation)
4. Markdown file is committed to the repo under a predictable path (e.g., docs/eks-upgrade-checklist.md)
5. Checklist is versioned — filename or frontmatter reflects the EKS target version (e.g., 1.32-to-1.33)
Story 2: Build Validation Script to Parse and Execute Checklist
As a platform engineer,
I want a script that reads the markdown checklist and executes each validation check
programmatically,
So that upgrade readiness is automatically verified without manual review.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
1. Script parses the markdown checklist and maps each item to a corresponding automated check (bash,
Python, or kubectl command)
2. Each check produces a clear PASS / FAIL output with a reason
3. Script exits with a non-zero code if any check fails
4. Results are printed in a structured format (e.g., table or JSON) suitable for Jenkins logs
5. Script is runnable locally and in CI
Story 3: Integrate Validation Script into Jenkins Pipeline on PR Push
As a platform engineer,
I want the validation script triggered automatically when a PR is pushed,
So that every proposed EKS upgrade is validated before it can be merged.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
1. Jenkins pipeline is configured to trigger on PR push to the upgrade automation repo
2. Validation script runs as a dedicated stage (e.g., Validate Upgrade Checklist)
3. Jenkins stage consumes the correct checklist version based on the target EKS version in the PR
4. Pipeline status (pass/fail) is reported back to the PR as a GitHub/GitLab status check
5. Logs are captured and archived as a Jenkins artifact
Story 4: Implement Merge Gate — Block or Approve Based on Validation
Results
As a platform engineer,
I want the PR merge to be automatically approved or blocked based on validation script results,
So that no EKS upgrade proceeds to main unless all checklist gates pass.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
1. If all checks pass → PR is automatically approved and merged to main
2. If any check fails → PR merge is blocked, and a comment is posted on the PR listing the failed checks
3. Failed PR is not auto-closed — it stays open for remediation
4. Notifications sent to the team (Slack or email) on both outcomes
5. Merge gate logic is idempotent — re-pushing after a fix re-triggers validation cleanly
SUGGESTED ONBOARDING ORDER
Story 1 → Story 2 → Story 3 → Story 4 is the recommended sequence. Story 1 is ideal as a first solo task — low risk,
gets your teammate familiar with the repo and the upgrade process context before touching any automation